headline: SYF Q4 Deep Dive: Flat Revenues and Cautious Growth Outlook Amid Product Expansion
summary: Consumer financial services company Synchrony Financial (NYSE:SYF) fell short of the markets revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales flat year on year at $3.79 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.18 per share was 7.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
